Marry Me White Bean Salad
  --Renu Anshie Dhar
 
1/3 c whole-milk plain strained (Greek-style) yogurt
2 tbsp mayo
2 tbsp sun-dried tomato oil (from tomatoes jar)
1 tbsp white-wine vinegar
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp Italian seasoning
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp crushed red pepper
1/4 tsp ground pepper
2x15 oz cans no-salt-added cannellini beans, rinsed
1 small red bell pepper, chopped (~1 1/4 c) 
1/2 c chopped drained julienne-cut sun-dried tomatoes in oil with herbs
2 medium scallions, chopped (1/4 c)
2 tbsp chopped fresh basil
2 tbsp pine nuts, toasted

Combine yogurt, mayo, sun-dried tomato oil, vinegar, garlic powder, Italian seasoning, and salt, crushed red pepper, and black pepper in a large bowl; stir well. Add rinsed beans, chopped bell pepper, chopped sun-dried tomatoes, chopped scallions and basil to the yogurt mixture; stir to combine. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 min (and up to 1 day). Sprinkle with pine nuts. 

Notes: can use chickpeas or butter beans, but texture might be off
